<br />
    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2"><br />
The strategy of the free peoples side can be summed up by one word: burn.<br />
This is usually how the deck works, but it can change given the scenario.<br />
 Get Sent back in play and saved from the fire in your hand, sack gandalf and pull out mithrandir, shadow fax and another saved from.<br />
Next turn, sack smeagol and get the gollum cards you need the most, and another saved from.<br />
next turn, sack whatever crappy gandalf companion is out (erland, ghan, quick) to get out radagast and treebeard (or use awinl).<br />
The idea is to set up however you want as fast as possible and leave nothing but shadow cards in your deck.<br />
<br />
The shadow side is killer. <br />
Use slippery as fishes to help stinker win, and lay on the burdens via his text and nasty foul hobbits.<br />
Also use heavy burden and not yet vanquished to corrupt. Shelob can stop the biggest companion from fighting to help gollum win.<br />
I put in sweeter meats to help gollum  survive to the regroup phase and use heavy burden. <br />
